    <text type="letter">
        <body> 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00544.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>   
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.</name>
                    <name type="place">Asylum for the Insane</name>
                    <name type="place">London.</name>
                    <name type="place">Ontario</name>
                    <name type="place">London, Ont.,<ptr target="loc.07287_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1888-12-24"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>24 Dec<handShift
                            rend="printed"/> 188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8<ptr
                            target="loc.07287_n2"/></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours of 21<ptr target="loc.07287_n3"/> containing Mrs O'Connor's<ptr target="n4137"/>
                letter this moment to hand (noon Monday). O'C.<ptr target="n2002"/> has wonderful
                    <hi rend="underline">grit</hi> and will make a hard fight yet&#8212;We will
                continue to wish him God speed and ourselves hope for the best. Poor Mrs O'C. too,
                what noble courage and determination she has! She is as grand as he is, as grand as
                    any.<ptr target="loc.07287_n4"/> W<hi rend="underline">m</hi> Gurd<ptr
                    target="n4284"/> is here, arrived yesterday without letter or warning, just
                walked in. All seems to be going on as it should with the meter but slow,
                slow,&#8212;We propose now to make it safe in Canada and western Europe and<pb
                    xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_es.00545.jpg" type="verso"/> then proceed to
                Philadelphia to lay it before experts and capitalists&#8212;perhaps establish a Co.
                to manufacture. I cannot tell how long it may take us yet to get to Phil<hi
                rend="underline">a</hi> but I think we ought to be there in the course of
                January. I trust to find you in good shape then. Nesbit<ptr target="n4153"/> (the other partner) will
                likely to be here very soon after Xmas we shall then settle on our immediate
                course</p>
            <p>A lovely bright warm day. Would rather however have snow, sleighing and cold at Xmas
                time</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>A good Xmas and Love to you</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
